    <persName>
        <forename>Patrick</forename>
        <surname>Neill</surname>
    </persName>
    
    <note type="dates"><date>1776–1851</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Printer. Vice-president of the Botanical Society of Edinburgh, 1836. Founder member of the Caledonian Horticultural Society and secretary for forty years. Collected Scottish plants and had a garden at Canonmills. Promoted the establishment of the Edinburgh Zoological Garden.</p></note>
